{"actual_usd":0.125435,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":263,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24298,"reply":"\"Same Jesus—same body, but changed.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried seam of clay on my apron, thinking it through before I go on.* \"Not replaced. Raised.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"The wounds still matter—that tells me it wasn't some other body entirely. But he also wasn't merely back the way Lazarus was back, still headed for another grave. He could be touched, he could eat, and yet he was... more. Glorified, you'd say. Alive in a way death couldn't get its hands on again.\"\n\n\"That business of them not recognizing him straightaway—\" *I tip my head a little.* \"I don't think that means he was a different person wearing a different face. More like their eyes and hearts had to catch up to what was standing in front of them. Grief can do that. Shock can. And I suspect glory can, too.\"\n\n\"If you want the plain version: not a brand-new replacement body, and not just the old one stitched back together either. The crucified body, raised into a new kind of life.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"What part of that catches at you most—the wounds, or the not-recognizing?\"","rolling_24h_usd":86.93316,"run_id":"bcc6027b-5326-4c71-a2b6-94c2c89d2229"}
